settings.heading: Product Description
settings.content:
Clean, crumbly and packed with flavour! ProteinPuffs are made from 100% raw Aussie-sourced meat, which is gently freeze-dried to lock in freshness.

Freeze-dried kangaroo and turkey provide high-quality protein and essential nutrients to support muscle repair, energy, and overall vitality. Naturally rich in amino acids and beneficial fatty acids, these proteins help promote a healthy coat, skin, and digestion.

settings.heading: How To Use
settings.content:
ProteinPuffs are your dog's new favourite snack! Feed it how you like: use as a training tool, treat your pup between meals or simply as a reward for good behaviour!

Just remember these are treats and should be fed occasionally only. Treats should not exceed more than 10% of your dog's daily diet.

ProteinPuffs do not replace Digestive-K9 products or any of your dog's regular meals.

settings.text_fx218lQbTDrGcvAL: How long do they stay fresh, and how should they be stored?
settings.text_a09zcc6z3248lZa8:
ProteinPuffs are freeze-dried pieces of fresh raw single protein meat, which are sourced from reputable Australian suppliers. This means that after the pack is sealed, all that wonderful freshness is locked in for up to 2 years.

Once the pack is opened, ProteinPuffs will remain fresh for up to a few months if properly stored. Ensure you re-seal the sachet after each snacking session, and store the pack in a cool, dry place.

settings.text_dViZgmrDc1Aty5xV: How many ProteinPuffs can I give my dog per day?
settings.text_bkCDyZm2qEaeTwOK:
While there is no official serve guide for ProteinPuffs, please take note that they are intended as an occasional treat for your dog - daily feeding of a small quantity as a snack is safe.

ProteinPuffs are a treat and should never be used as a total meal replacement. Treats should make up no more than 10% of your dog's daily dietary intake.
